```java
private boolean toStringEquals(Matcher m, Object arg) {
    return StringDescription.toString(m).equals(arg.toString());
}
```

The problem occurs when `arg` is `null`. When `arg` is `null`, calling `arg.toString()` will throw a `NullPointerException`. The test `shouldWorkFineWhenGivenArgIsNull` expects the method to handle null arguments gracefully, but currently it doesn't.

